WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.552 --> 00:53.970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:54.054 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

01:09.527 --> 01:10.779
What should I choose?

01:13.531 --> 01:14.699
It might look pretty.

01:14.783 --> 01:16.367
We're totally like a couple.

01:16.951 --> 01:18.244
So delicious!

01:19.579 --> 01:20.830
How pretty.

01:23.208 --> 01:25.418
Na-hyun, I'm so excited.

01:26.252 --> 01:27.253
Me too.

01:27.337 --> 01:30.006
What else do you want to do?
Let's do everything you want.

01:30.840 --> 01:33.968
How about another
roller coaster ride then?

01:34.052 --> 01:35.053
Sure.

01:43.353 --> 01:44.979
If I act strange in any way,

01:45.563 --> 01:47.232
splash that water on me.

01:49.609 --> 01:50.610
Oh, no.

01:57.867 --> 01:58.868
No, please.

02:00.203 --> 02:01.329
Don't go.

02:06.459 --> 02:07.460
Na-hyun.

02:08.211 --> 02:11.339
We'll meet again.

02:11.422 --> 02:12.257
No.

02:13.758 --> 02:14.968
I don't believe it.

02:16.094 --> 02:17.095
I will

02:18.263 --> 02:20.557
spend enough time with you

02:21.683 --> 02:23.017
before I pass on.

02:27.480 --> 02:28.523
I promise.

03:32.879 --> 03:34.339
I could drive myself.

03:43.556 --> 03:45.058
PASSENGER'S SEAT

03:49.604 --> 03:50.980
Where's my sister?

03:51.606 --> 03:52.857
Is she in this car?

03:55.485 --> 03:57.987
Yes. I'm right here, Na-hyun.

03:59.614 --> 04:01.908
She's seated right behind you.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.251
How do you get possessed?

04:12.961 --> 04:14.671
From my experience so far,

04:15.171 --> 04:18.758
it happens when a ghost is faced
with something they love or hate.

04:19.384 --> 04:22.971
But what's important is
that it can't be done intentionally.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.640
Without being possessed,

04:25.723 --> 04:28.726
is it impossible for me to communicate
with them or even touch them?

04:29.686 --> 04:30.645
Na-hyun…

04:31.646 --> 04:32.814
That's right.

04:36.401 --> 04:37.402
I see.

04:44.033 --> 04:45.034
Attorney Shin,

04:46.035 --> 04:47.370
would you like to be with me tonight?

05:10.143 --> 05:11.436
It fits you right.

05:12.020 --> 05:13.146
Come here.

05:17.066 --> 05:19.193
<i>Did you get the electric razor as a gift?</i>

05:20.862 --> 05:22.238
<i>You know,</i>

05:22.322 --> 05:26.993
<i>Su-jeong saved her pocket money</i>
<i>from that day to buy it.</i>

05:27.744 --> 05:29.620
<i>The court finds the defendant guilty.</i>

05:30.580 --> 05:31.789
<i>Therefore, this court hereby…</i>

05:31.873 --> 05:34.167
-Is it you, So-hyun?
<i>-…sentences defendant Baek Hong-seok</i>

05:34.250 --> 05:35.960
<i>to 15 years in prison.</i>

05:36.044 --> 05:38.004
It's still I-rang.

05:39.213 --> 05:40.590
That's strange.

05:40.673 --> 05:44.469
<i>While his fury over his daughter's death</i>
<i>can be considered as a mitigating factor…</i>

05:45.094 --> 05:48.139
Is this the show you wanted to watch?

05:48.931 --> 05:51.559
Yes, I died
and couldn't watch it to the end.

05:55.772 --> 05:57.190
I'm stepping outside for a second.

05:57.273 --> 05:58.649
Where are you going?

05:58.733 --> 05:59.901
To buy a board game.

06:00.485 --> 06:02.195
We used to play Monopoly often.

06:02.779 --> 06:04.280
-Oh.
-I'll be back.

06:06.824 --> 06:08.076
Monopoly?

06:08.826 --> 06:09.827
Yes.

06:12.163 --> 06:13.122
-Six.
-Six.

06:15.208 --> 06:16.584
Two, three, four…

06:17.627 --> 06:19.378
-Seoul.
-That's mine.

06:20.088 --> 06:21.672
What now?

06:21.756 --> 06:24.967
-You need to pay the toll.
-It's just two million won.

06:25.051 --> 06:26.469
-Two million won?
-Yup.

06:27.845 --> 06:29.931
-Ten, twenty, thirty…
-Got enough?

06:31.682 --> 06:32.975
You're bankrupt.

06:34.894 --> 06:35.728
Give me your arm.

06:35.812 --> 06:37.313
My arm? Why…

06:37.396 --> 06:38.397
-Loser gets hit.
-Loser gets hit.

06:42.068 --> 06:45.029
Fine, as long as the two of you
are having fun.

06:45.113 --> 06:46.072
Go ahead.

06:47.031 --> 06:48.074
Do it hard.

06:52.370 --> 06:53.496
One more round?

06:54.372 --> 06:58.000
All right, I get to escape
if I roll doubles.

07:03.005 --> 07:04.173
-Wow!
-Doubles!

07:05.550 --> 07:08.177
-Eight.
-One, two, three, four, five, six,

07:08.261 --> 07:09.512
seven, eight…

07:10.638 --> 07:12.640
Oh, man. That's mine again.

07:12.723 --> 07:14.392
Incredible! You're bankrupt again.

07:16.185 --> 07:17.061
This makes no sense.

07:17.645 --> 07:18.479
Your arm.

07:20.773 --> 07:22.775
-Is it you, So-hyun?
-No.

07:25.528 --> 07:26.362
"Moving day."

07:26.446 --> 07:28.322
"Go back two spaces."

07:28.406 --> 07:29.615
-Paris.
-Paris.

07:31.367 --> 07:32.452
Bankrupt.

07:34.454 --> 07:35.538
Na-hyun.

07:51.762 --> 07:53.806
New York. That's mine.

07:55.558 --> 07:58.144
That'll be 3.1 million won.

07:58.227 --> 08:00.855
Three point one million…
You don't have enough?

08:02.607 --> 08:03.816
Give me your arm.

08:04.442 --> 08:05.568
You won't hit me, will you?

08:05.651 --> 08:07.945
Don't look at me like that. It won't work.

08:08.029 --> 08:08.863
Come on.

08:16.954 --> 08:18.039
Wait!

08:24.629 --> 08:27.423
Han Na-hyun,
I'm letting you go this one time.

08:37.558 --> 08:39.352
Let me see your arm for a sec.

08:43.856 --> 08:45.983
She didn't hit you at all.

08:47.318 --> 08:48.861
She tried,

08:48.945 --> 08:50.196
but she missed.

08:50.279 --> 08:52.156
That's so not fair!

08:53.741 --> 08:56.077
I get it now. You guys are
in cahoots together, aren't you?

09:07.964 --> 09:09.507
First off, your sister…

09:09.590 --> 09:12.885
wanted to go on a palace tour
while wearing <i>hanbok</i>.

09:13.636 --> 09:14.679
Right.

09:15.596 --> 09:19.100
The only places she went were
school, cram school, and home.

09:21.852 --> 09:22.853
Oh, sorry.

09:24.105 --> 09:24.939
It's okay.

09:26.524 --> 09:28.276
So,

09:28.359 --> 09:31.654
what should we start with?

09:32.446 --> 09:34.532
A palace tour?

09:34.615 --> 09:36.325
Camping…

09:39.579 --> 09:41.205
Oh, I'm sorry.

09:44.333 --> 09:45.585
Why don't we get some shut-eye?

09:46.252 --> 09:48.254
No, we don't have time to waste.

09:49.380 --> 09:50.881
Let's fight it off.

09:51.674 --> 09:52.592
Next.

09:55.928 --> 09:57.680
A college festival…

10:07.356 --> 10:09.650
Why don't we sleep for just ten minutes?

10:10.234 --> 10:12.820
-Just ten minutes.
-Yes, just ten minutes.

10:53.235 --> 10:55.196
Did you have a comfortable flight, Father?

10:55.279 --> 10:56.405
-Please get on.
-I'm okay.

11:09.251 --> 11:10.378
Ah, yes.

11:33.401 --> 11:36.654
Father, the whole staff is waiting
in the main conference room.

11:36.737 --> 11:39.407
I instructed everyone to be there
from newcomers to executives.

11:39.490 --> 11:41.659
They'd appreciate
a word of encouragement from you.

11:41.742 --> 11:43.327
What for? They must be busy.

11:44.036 --> 11:45.538
Tell them to go back to work.

11:46.497 --> 11:47.331
Pardon?

11:47.415 --> 11:48.791
Let's just go have lunch.

11:50.626 --> 11:52.545
Oh, silly me.

11:52.628 --> 11:55.005
You didn't like the airline food, did you?
Let me take you somewhere nice--

11:55.089 --> 11:56.757
I have a place in mind. Let's go there.

12:13.023 --> 12:14.942
Is this the place you wanted to come?

12:15.025 --> 12:16.026
Yes.

12:17.069 --> 12:18.404
Welcome.

12:19.530 --> 12:20.739
Chief Prosecutor Yang?

12:21.323 --> 12:23.159
How have you been, Gyeong-hwa?

12:23.242 --> 12:24.201
Goodness.

12:25.411 --> 12:26.495
Do-kyung, say hello to her.

12:26.579 --> 12:28.831
She's the wife of a prosecutor
who was once close to me.

12:29.457 --> 12:30.791
This is my son.

12:33.586 --> 12:34.587
Nice to meet you.

12:36.380 --> 12:37.798
Nice to meet you too.

12:52.229 --> 12:54.398
You're still as good a cook as ever.

12:55.232 --> 12:57.193
I'm glad it's to your liking.

12:58.319 --> 13:00.905
If you aren't too busy,
why don't you sit down for a moment?

13:02.323 --> 13:03.157
Oh.

13:03.782 --> 13:04.783
Sure.

13:06.702 --> 13:08.370
Would you like me to wait outside, Father?

13:08.454 --> 13:10.956
No, you'd better stay and listen.

13:12.875 --> 13:16.086
I collapsed a year ago.

13:17.087 --> 13:19.256
I had heart surgery,
and now I'm recovering.

13:19.340 --> 13:20.925
Oh, no.

13:21.008 --> 13:24.345
Then, you shouldn't eat anything
spicy or salty like this spicy pork.

13:24.428 --> 13:27.264
No, I finally feel like living.

13:28.849 --> 13:29.850
Gosh.

13:32.228 --> 13:33.729
As I entered the operating room,

13:35.356 --> 13:37.483
I thought I could die on the table.

13:38.692 --> 13:41.111
My life flashed before my eyes.

13:41.946 --> 13:43.989
Then, I was reminded of Gi-jung.

13:46.867 --> 13:47.993
I'm here to apologize.

13:48.827 --> 13:52.206
I failed to look after Gi-jung
at the time.

13:52.748 --> 13:54.124
I'm sorry, Gyeong-hwa.

13:54.667 --> 13:57.419
No, please don't say that.

13:57.503 --> 14:00.422
You tried your best to defend him,

14:00.506 --> 14:04.134
and even after he died,
you offered help many times,

14:04.218 --> 14:05.844
which I turned down.

14:06.387 --> 14:09.098
I should've rather expressed my gratitude,

14:10.349 --> 14:12.977
but I was too busy with life.

14:13.060 --> 14:13.978
No.

14:14.645 --> 14:16.146
Had I known a bit earlier…

14:16.230 --> 14:17.606
Oh.

14:17.690 --> 14:20.651
Please stop.
You're making me feel ashamed.

14:23.070 --> 14:27.658
I heard I-rang applied for Taebaek
while I was in the States.

14:27.741 --> 14:31.287
And that the interviewers
were quite rude to him.

14:31.370 --> 14:32.746
Were you aware of it?

14:37.960 --> 14:39.879
JOB APPLICATION
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

14:40.671 --> 14:42.923
Your concern is on me.

14:43.507 --> 14:45.509
I should've kept my employees
under better control.

14:46.093 --> 14:47.136
I apologize.

14:51.849 --> 14:52.892
I apologize.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.936
No, it's all right.

14:56.437 --> 14:59.023
I-rang and I don't mind.

14:59.106 --> 15:00.774
Please don't worry.

15:00.858 --> 15:01.984
May I ask

15:02.776 --> 15:05.195
where he's working at the moment?

15:05.279 --> 15:06.530
Well,

15:06.614 --> 15:09.700
he's running a small law office alone.

15:17.207 --> 15:18.500
Here.

15:18.584 --> 15:21.378
Will you tell him to visit me sometime?

15:21.462 --> 15:25.007
It's not easy to run a business alone.

15:25.925 --> 15:28.218
There must be something
I can help him with.

15:44.985 --> 15:46.445
Soap bubbles!

16:05.422 --> 16:06.966
PALACE TOUR WHILE WEARING HANBOK

16:10.719 --> 16:11.804
<i>Taking picture.</i>

16:14.682 --> 16:15.891
I like this one and this one.

16:15.975 --> 16:17.059
Hey, this is pretty.

16:29.863 --> 16:31.073
It's cool and windy.

16:31.156 --> 16:32.700
I know, it's so refreshing.

16:32.783 --> 16:34.576
Hey, it's beautiful.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.328
The gust is blowing hard.

16:37.913 --> 16:39.748
WATCH SUNSET
FROM HOT AIR BALLOON

16:39.832 --> 16:41.041
Try this.

16:44.920 --> 16:45.838
It's in.

16:48.424 --> 16:49.550
Awesome.

17:03.230 --> 17:04.106
Cross.

17:04.189 --> 17:05.399
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

17:14.658 --> 17:16.702
CAMPING UNDER THE STARS

17:17.286 --> 17:19.038
We had such a clear view of the stars.

17:19.121 --> 17:20.205
I know, right?

17:21.582 --> 17:24.084
But I got so many mosquito bites.

17:24.168 --> 17:25.502
Mister.

17:27.171 --> 17:29.256
I want to go there.

17:30.758 --> 17:31.592
Are you sure?

17:32.176 --> 17:33.594
What is it? What did she say?

17:34.762 --> 17:36.638
She wants to go there.

17:38.557 --> 17:39.808
She can't.

17:39.892 --> 17:41.602
She's still a minor.

17:42.811 --> 17:47.107
I hear adults open up after a few drinks.

17:47.858 --> 17:50.110
I want to know how she really feels.

17:52.446 --> 17:54.239
She just wants to feel the vibe.

17:55.074 --> 17:56.992
I think it's okay.

17:58.118 --> 18:00.579
-All right, cheers.
-Cheers.

18:02.664 --> 18:03.874
So-hyun?

18:05.167 --> 18:06.043
It's me.

18:08.003 --> 18:09.421
I can tell.

18:13.967 --> 18:15.761
Your fried chicken is here.

18:22.059 --> 18:24.144
It looks so good.

18:29.316 --> 18:30.984
You can have all the wings.

18:31.068 --> 18:32.111
Are you serious?

18:33.112 --> 18:35.197
Then, you can have the drumsticks.

18:36.824 --> 18:38.200
Let's enjoy!

18:46.750 --> 18:48.043
It's to die for.

18:53.006 --> 18:54.424
Why aren't you eating?

18:55.008 --> 18:55.884
I'm happy.

18:56.510 --> 18:57.594
You can eat all you want.

18:58.470 --> 19:00.556
Na-hyun, you sound all grown up.

19:01.723 --> 19:03.225
It was worth looking after you.

19:07.229 --> 19:10.774
Anyway, how did you end up
becoming an attorney?

19:11.650 --> 19:13.068
Why didn't you become a singer?

19:13.986 --> 19:15.445
Competition was so fierce.

19:16.405 --> 19:18.532
Where did all that confidence go, Na-hyun?

19:20.951 --> 19:22.452
There wasn't some grand reason.

19:23.453 --> 19:26.165
I just became an attorney
because it looked cool.

19:29.960 --> 19:32.754
I have another question.

19:34.006 --> 19:35.132
What is it?

19:35.966 --> 19:37.843
What's with you and our parents?

19:38.760 --> 19:39.678
What do you mean?

19:39.761 --> 19:41.680
You don't answer their calls.

19:43.265 --> 19:44.683
That's simply because I'm busy.

19:47.186 --> 19:48.228
Are you sure?

19:48.312 --> 19:50.063
It happens in life.

19:57.654 --> 19:58.655
Sorry.

19:59.615 --> 20:01.241
I'm going to go to the bathroom.

20:20.010 --> 20:21.011
Wait.

20:21.595 --> 20:22.512
Where's your sister?

20:23.180 --> 20:24.097
She's in the bathroom.

20:28.477 --> 20:31.438
Did you talk enough with your sister?

20:32.773 --> 20:33.607
Yes.

20:35.192 --> 20:36.151
That's good.

20:37.152 --> 20:38.946
I'll be right back.

20:39.029 --> 20:41.406
Let's just leave all together
when Attorney Han returns.

20:41.490 --> 20:44.534
Geez, you're so slow-witted.

20:45.077 --> 20:47.037
I'm giving you some space alone with her.

20:48.205 --> 20:49.039
What?

20:49.122 --> 20:52.626
I can see through Na-hyun
just by looking at her gaze.

20:54.211 --> 20:55.879
When she's with you,

20:56.588 --> 20:57.923
she laughs.

21:00.133 --> 21:02.427
While I'm away,

21:03.637 --> 21:06.890
could you cheer her up a little?

21:07.766 --> 21:08.892
Okay.

21:08.976 --> 21:11.645
I didn't know I had that kind of talent,

21:13.438 --> 21:14.898
but I'll give it a try.

21:19.152 --> 21:21.029
Okay. I'll tell you later if I see it.

21:21.113 --> 21:23.073
-So where were you going again?
-Cram school.

21:23.156 --> 21:24.574
-You? Cram school?
-Yeah, cram school.

21:24.658 --> 21:26.076
What's wrong with that?

21:27.202 --> 21:28.912
-What do you want for dinner?
-<i>Jjajangmyeon</i>.

21:28.996 --> 21:29.997
-<i>Jjajangmyeon</i>?
-Yes!

21:30.080 --> 21:31.832
Let's have that and <i>tangsuyuk</i> too.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.546
Is she not here yet?

21:38.213 --> 21:41.133
She said she'd be away for a minute.
She'll be back soon.

21:45.470 --> 21:48.598
Attorney Han,
have you ever had an egg bomb before?

21:55.272 --> 21:56.106
Now,

21:56.940 --> 21:58.525
You take the egg…

22:01.945 --> 22:03.947
It really is like an egg.

22:04.489 --> 22:07.284
Here comes your egg!

22:07.367 --> 22:11.246
Here comes your egg bomb
that will cheer you up if you drink!

22:11.330 --> 22:12.831
Where did you learn how to do this?

22:12.914 --> 22:15.542
I studied how. Shall we clink?

22:16.668 --> 22:18.086
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

22:27.554 --> 22:28.430
It's good.

22:32.559 --> 22:35.353
Come to think of it,
I didn't even get to thank you.

22:36.980 --> 22:41.276
Thanks to you,
I'm having a great time with my sister.

22:43.278 --> 22:45.530
Thank you so much, Attorney Shin.

22:45.614 --> 22:47.407
Don't mention it.

22:48.283 --> 22:49.618
I already know.

22:49.701 --> 22:50.869
No.

22:52.287 --> 22:54.956
It's never enough to say,

22:55.665 --> 22:57.375
"I'm sorry," "thank you,"
and "I love you."

22:58.543 --> 23:00.837
After time, you only regret

23:01.755 --> 23:03.423
that you didn't say it more.

23:19.356 --> 23:20.774
She has to go, doesn't she?

23:23.485 --> 23:24.820
I mean, my sister.

23:27.739 --> 23:29.491
Does she have to?

23:30.909 --> 23:32.744
The ghosts who visited me…

23:34.412 --> 23:36.039
They all passed on.

23:37.749 --> 23:41.253
The priest also said it was only right.

23:42.504 --> 23:43.964
So she has to leave.

23:48.927 --> 23:50.887
Maybe she could stay.

23:50.971 --> 23:53.557
She could just live with me by my side.

23:53.640 --> 23:55.517
Maybe,

23:56.601 --> 23:57.602
but

23:59.646 --> 24:04.067
<i>I doubt staying in this world</i>
<i>is good for her.</i>

24:07.404 --> 24:09.489
Even if she stays,

24:10.907 --> 24:13.285
you won't be able to talk to her
or even see her

24:14.536 --> 24:15.996
without me.

24:27.674 --> 24:31.094
Let me be alone with her
without you today.

24:33.013 --> 24:34.181
Will you be okay?

24:35.182 --> 24:37.517
Of course. We're sisters.

24:40.937 --> 24:41.897
Okay.

24:49.696 --> 24:50.697
Bye.

24:52.699 --> 24:54.201
Don't you worry.

24:54.284 --> 24:55.285
Okay.

25:27.359 --> 25:28.860
So-hyun, are you here?

25:39.996 --> 25:42.123
It does feel awkward
being unable to see you.

25:44.251 --> 25:45.460
But it's kind of fun too.

25:48.255 --> 25:49.923
We better make some rules.

25:51.132 --> 25:54.219
Sit across from me when we sit at a table.

25:54.302 --> 25:57.097
When we walk or sit side by side,

25:58.014 --> 25:59.140
be on my right.

26:00.433 --> 26:01.434
What do you say?

26:05.230 --> 26:06.856
So, that's decided.

26:12.028 --> 26:13.697
"Move to any space you want."

26:17.033 --> 26:18.493
How about the States?

26:18.576 --> 26:20.161
You wanted to go to the States.

26:20.245 --> 26:22.163
NEW YORK

26:42.017 --> 26:43.518
I better wash up.

27:22.766 --> 27:24.100
I'm home.

27:24.184 --> 27:25.560
Welcome back.

27:29.564 --> 27:31.358
What's that? Is it for a customer?

27:31.441 --> 27:34.527
No, it's a gift for someone.

27:35.737 --> 27:39.657
Wow. Flat tail, sirloin, and short plate?

27:40.533 --> 27:42.285
It's a high-end prime Korean beef set.

27:42.994 --> 27:44.412
Who is it for?

27:45.455 --> 27:47.582
For someone I know.

27:52.128 --> 27:53.671
TAEBAEK
CHAIRMAN YANG BYUNG-IL

27:57.759 --> 28:00.512
He used to be your dad's superior
back when he was a chief prosecutor.

28:01.137 --> 28:03.181
He was here to have lunch earlier today.

28:03.765 --> 28:06.601
He apologized for being inattentive.

28:06.684 --> 28:09.145
Why all of a sudden after 20 years?

28:09.729 --> 28:11.648
Because it's been 20 years.

28:12.399 --> 28:15.443
With age, you tend to regret
and blame yourself more.

28:16.111 --> 28:18.321
It must be the same for him.

28:19.364 --> 28:21.533
He wants to be of help
if it's not too late.

28:21.616 --> 28:23.952
So you send him a gift

28:24.035 --> 28:25.578
over a few empty words?

28:25.662 --> 28:28.039
He's recovering from a serious ailment.

28:28.123 --> 28:30.291
Quality meat will help him
build up his strength.

28:30.875 --> 28:32.252
Aren't you mad at all?

28:32.877 --> 28:35.463
Nobody came to Dad's funeral.

28:35.547 --> 28:39.634
Those cowards covered their own butts
after what happened to Dad.

28:39.718 --> 28:41.052
He was the only one

28:41.136 --> 28:44.472
who struggled to clear your dad's name
until the end.

28:45.265 --> 28:46.391
We should be grateful.

28:49.352 --> 28:50.478
Still, I hate it.

28:51.146 --> 28:52.647
Don't talk to me about him ever again.

29:10.999 --> 29:13.293
When did you come?

29:16.838 --> 29:18.214
What's wrong?

29:18.298 --> 29:19.799
Did something happen to Attorney Han?

29:22.635 --> 29:23.845
Nothing happened.

29:25.847 --> 29:27.265
Because nothing happened,

29:29.267 --> 29:31.686
I feel so bad for Na-hyun.

29:36.983 --> 29:38.443
So-hyun, are you here?

29:39.402 --> 29:40.278
Yes,

29:41.446 --> 29:42.739
I'm right here.

29:45.909 --> 29:48.161
It does feel awkward
being unable to see you.

29:48.745 --> 29:49.829
But it's kind of fun too.

29:50.705 --> 29:51.581
Me too.

29:54.167 --> 29:56.085
We better make some rules.

29:57.170 --> 30:00.131
Sit across from me when we sit at a table.

30:00.965 --> 30:03.802
When we walk or sit side by side,

30:04.677 --> 30:05.804
be on my right.

30:07.013 --> 30:07.889
What do you say?

30:11.810 --> 30:12.894
Sounds good.

30:15.814 --> 30:17.273
So, that's decided.

30:17.857 --> 30:20.026
Okay. That's decided.

30:23.196 --> 30:24.989
"Move to any space you want."

30:26.658 --> 30:30.119
How about the States?
You wanted to go to the States.

30:32.372 --> 30:33.623
I'm not going to the States.

30:37.919 --> 30:39.462
I want to stay by your side.

30:41.923 --> 30:43.800
Han So-hyun's favorite ice cream.

30:49.681 --> 30:50.515
Is it good?

30:55.687 --> 30:57.105
I better wash up.

31:18.751 --> 31:22.130
<i>She can't watch TV</i>
<i>or play Monopoly with me,</i>

31:23.298 --> 31:24.924
<i>but Na-hyun</i>

31:26.259 --> 31:30.179
<i>doesn't stop moving in case I feel bored.</i>

31:32.265 --> 31:34.642
She doesn't have to
bend over backwards like that.

31:36.811 --> 31:39.063
She's troubled because of me.

31:40.690 --> 31:41.941
That's so…

31:44.485 --> 31:45.653
heartbreaking.

31:59.334 --> 32:00.919
She's not troubled.

32:02.170 --> 32:03.338
She's anxious.

32:06.299 --> 32:07.508
I know.

32:08.593 --> 32:10.678
She's worried I might leave.

32:15.308 --> 32:17.936
That's exactly why I shouldn't stay here.

32:19.771 --> 32:21.648
Mister, you know what?

32:22.649 --> 32:24.817
I was

32:25.944 --> 32:27.862
truly happy

32:29.072 --> 32:30.782
to be with Na-hyun.

32:32.241 --> 32:36.037
I even hoped I could stay by her side…

32:38.206 --> 32:39.666
forever and ever.

32:44.045 --> 32:46.047
But seeing her today

32:47.590 --> 32:50.969
made me realize that I was wrong.

32:52.679 --> 32:54.639
A life with a ghost isn't for her.

32:56.224 --> 32:58.851
She needs to go back to her ordinary life.

33:02.188 --> 33:04.565
I'm done with my bucket list.

33:07.151 --> 33:08.277
Except just one thing.

33:09.946 --> 33:11.656
I have to do one last thing

33:13.408 --> 33:14.742
before I pass on.

33:15.576 --> 33:16.661
Wow.

33:16.744 --> 33:19.122
-Drumroll.
-What is this?

33:20.915 --> 33:22.625
-Ta-da!
-Ta-da!

33:22.709 --> 33:25.128
Here's seaweed soup made by Han Na-hyun.

33:27.130 --> 33:28.840
-Oh, my.
-How is it?

33:28.923 --> 33:31.342
Dear, the soup is too salty.

33:31.926 --> 33:33.302
Salty? I checked it myself.

33:33.386 --> 33:34.262
Goodness.

33:36.347 --> 33:37.682
I told you, it's salty.

33:39.350 --> 33:40.435
She can't hide it.

33:42.353 --> 33:44.605
It really is too salty,

33:44.689 --> 33:45.523
but it's good.

33:48.693 --> 33:50.403
-This is inedible.
-It needs more water.

33:50.486 --> 33:52.655
Right, bring some hot water.

33:52.739 --> 33:55.408
<i>-I think that's why I came here.</i>
-It's delicious.

33:56.200 --> 33:57.994
To help my family go back to before.

34:00.038 --> 34:00.913
Sure.

34:02.206 --> 34:05.084
If that's what you think, let's do it.

34:08.337 --> 34:10.715
But how should we do it?

34:13.885 --> 34:15.303
Oh, is there anything

34:15.845 --> 34:18.973
you might crave of your mom's food?

34:21.934 --> 34:23.436
There is one!

34:23.519 --> 34:24.937
-What is it?
-My mom's kimchi stew.

34:25.021 --> 34:26.272
-Kimchi stew?
-Yes.

34:26.355 --> 34:30.276
Pork kimchi stew. It's super delicious.

34:30.359 --> 34:33.321
Oh, pork kimchi stew?

34:33.404 --> 34:36.866
Yes, the amount of pork neck is
much more than the broth itself.

34:37.825 --> 34:39.202
My mouth is already watering.

34:40.578 --> 34:41.746
Sounds delicious.

34:43.331 --> 34:44.957
How appetizing…

34:45.458 --> 34:46.918
All right, then.

34:47.543 --> 34:50.129
Let's… go with that.

34:50.213 --> 34:53.049
Just the thought of it already excites me.

34:54.967 --> 34:57.386
Must that kimchi stew

34:57.470 --> 34:59.722
have pork in it?

34:59.806 --> 35:02.725
Yes, there's much more pork neck
than the amount of broth.

35:02.809 --> 35:04.435
MOM'S KIMCHI STEW

35:04.519 --> 35:05.937
Our mom's kimchi stew?

35:06.979 --> 35:10.274
Yes, she forgot to write it
on her bucket list.

35:14.612 --> 35:15.696
Will you do it for her?

35:19.158 --> 35:20.118
Honey.

35:22.328 --> 35:24.747
I've got to tell Na-hyun.

35:26.332 --> 35:29.710
You know I've been wanting to tell her,

35:30.628 --> 35:31.712
but I couldn't.

35:32.255 --> 35:33.214
I'll do it now.

35:34.507 --> 35:37.218
Are you sure about this?

35:38.386 --> 35:39.262
Yes.

35:40.680 --> 35:42.140
Remember the day

35:42.223 --> 35:46.310
you dropped a customer off
at the former shaman's house?

35:46.394 --> 35:47.770
Since that day,

35:49.605 --> 35:52.859
I keep feeling like
something has to change.

36:00.116 --> 36:02.076
NA-HYUN

36:02.160 --> 36:03.244
It's Na-hyun.

36:04.287 --> 36:05.288
-Pick up.
-Okay.

36:07.832 --> 36:09.167
H-Hello?

36:09.250 --> 36:12.086
<i>Dad, is Mom home?</i>

36:12.170 --> 36:13.504
Your mom?

36:13.588 --> 36:15.506
Yes, she is. Hold on.
Do you want to talk to her?

36:15.590 --> 36:18.426
<i>No, I'm arriving home in five minutes.</i>

36:18.509 --> 36:19.760
What? Five…

36:20.303 --> 36:21.304
Oh, okay…

36:23.139 --> 36:25.141
She's arriving in five minutes.

36:25.725 --> 36:27.518
I'll ask her to pack the kimchi stew.

36:27.602 --> 36:29.520
Wait here. I'll be back soon.

36:29.604 --> 36:30.980
Take your time.

36:32.773 --> 36:36.068
I mean, let your mother take time
to make it delicious.

36:38.029 --> 36:41.240
Your sister is very excited, you see.

36:44.952 --> 36:45.912
Okay.

36:47.496 --> 36:48.706
Good luck, Na-hyun!

37:15.233 --> 37:17.276
Hi, Na-hyun. Come on in.

37:19.779 --> 37:20.988
Will she be okay?

37:22.865 --> 37:25.534
I'm worried
as to how their conversation will go.

37:28.287 --> 37:30.331
She may push them away at first,

37:30.414 --> 37:33.042
but they'll eventually come
to understand each other.

37:33.834 --> 37:35.169
That's how a family is.

37:36.754 --> 37:37.755
Let's have faith

37:38.547 --> 37:39.632
in your parents

37:39.715 --> 37:42.510
and your sister.

37:50.518 --> 37:55.231
I'm so delighted to know
that you crave my kimchi stew.

37:55.314 --> 37:57.316
Me too.

37:57.400 --> 37:59.694
We haven't eaten together
in such a long time.

38:00.987 --> 38:01.821
Hold on.

38:02.905 --> 38:04.115
Let me set the table.

38:04.198 --> 38:06.117
No, just pack some for me.

38:06.701 --> 38:07.618
I'll eat it at home.

38:09.996 --> 38:13.541
Why? You're here after a long time.
Stay and have dinner with us.

38:14.125 --> 38:15.835
Right, it'll be ready soon.

38:15.918 --> 38:17.920
Honey. It's almost ready, right?

38:18.004 --> 38:20.006
-Yes.
-I had a late lunch.

38:20.923 --> 38:23.509
Pack some for me.
I'll have it at home tomorrow.

38:24.427 --> 38:28.431
Well, okay.
Kimchi stew is always better the next day.

38:41.152 --> 38:42.153
Well…

38:44.780 --> 38:45.948
Na-hyun.

38:46.657 --> 38:48.159
There's something

38:48.242 --> 38:51.412
I must tell you today.

39:06.677 --> 39:07.720
Na-hyun.

39:08.929 --> 39:10.431
I'm…

39:11.599 --> 39:12.516
sorry.

39:20.733 --> 39:22.651
I forgot I had plans.

39:23.569 --> 39:25.446
-I'll just go.
-That day,

39:26.030 --> 39:27.823
in front of the operating room…

39:30.826 --> 39:32.745
-Oh no, So-hyun.
-She'll be okay.

39:33.537 --> 39:34.789
Doctor.

39:38.751 --> 39:40.503
-I'm sorry.
-What?

39:42.046 --> 39:45.049
-Doctor?
-Oh, my goodness. So-hyun…

39:45.132 --> 39:47.676
-Oh no, honey!
-Honey!

39:47.760 --> 39:49.428
How do we go on!

39:50.930 --> 39:52.348
What do we do?

39:55.101 --> 39:57.311
What are we supposed to do?

39:57.395 --> 39:59.438
Our girl…

40:00.731 --> 40:01.565
Mom.

40:04.693 --> 40:05.778
Mom.

40:06.612 --> 40:07.613
Mom.

40:08.531 --> 40:11.659
Why did you have to take her
to the concert?

40:12.493 --> 40:14.870
You could've just performed
by yourself in a band.

40:14.954 --> 40:17.498
Why did you have to take your sister?

40:21.877 --> 40:23.587
I lost myself for a second.

40:25.423 --> 40:27.842
What I said was absurd, Na-hyun.

40:30.594 --> 40:31.971
What are you talking about?

40:34.056 --> 40:35.683
I don't follow.

40:36.934 --> 40:38.644
It's my fault.

40:40.104 --> 40:42.231
You were shocked more than anyone else,

40:42.314 --> 40:44.233
but instead of comforting you,

40:44.900 --> 40:46.694
I blamed you.

40:48.320 --> 40:49.447
And yet…

40:53.117 --> 40:55.536
knowing that you were
closing yourself off,

40:58.038 --> 41:00.291
I waited for time to resolve it all.

41:00.374 --> 41:01.333
No.

41:06.505 --> 41:08.215
I killed So-hyun.

41:12.219 --> 41:14.013
I killed your daughter.

41:18.559 --> 41:19.393
Na-hyun.

41:24.315 --> 41:26.317
So don't forgive me.

41:31.655 --> 41:33.199
It's not your fault.

41:34.992 --> 41:36.243
What happened

41:37.411 --> 41:39.079
was never your fault, Na-hyun.

41:40.414 --> 41:41.415
Our dear daughter…

41:42.208 --> 41:43.417
For all this time,

41:44.376 --> 41:46.128
you must've suffered so much alone.

41:47.671 --> 41:48.964
I'm…

41:49.048 --> 41:50.674
I'm so sorry.

41:57.389 --> 41:58.390
Honey.

41:59.892 --> 42:03.729
Let's give her some time to think.

42:27.670 --> 42:29.129
I feel so sorry…

42:33.425 --> 42:35.719
that I don't know what to say.

42:42.434 --> 42:43.727
You don't have to do anything.

42:44.770 --> 42:45.688
All we need

42:46.689 --> 42:48.649
is for you to be our daughter.

42:49.900 --> 42:51.277
That's more than enough, Na-hyun.

42:53.320 --> 42:55.322
Our sweet daughter.

42:57.324 --> 43:00.202
Thank you for opening up to us.

43:00.786 --> 43:02.705
Thank you so much, Na-hyun.

43:49.209 --> 43:51.879
<i>It's never enough to say,</i>

43:51.962 --> 43:53.881
"I'm sorry," "thank you,"
and "I love you."

43:55.090 --> 43:57.259
After time, you only regret

43:58.302 --> 43:59.762
that you didn't say it more.

44:18.280 --> 44:20.366
-Mom.
-What is it?

44:22.201 --> 44:25.162
I'm sorry
for getting angry at you yesterday.

44:26.497 --> 44:28.207
This is unusual of you.

44:28.832 --> 44:30.292
Well, someone told me

44:31.377 --> 44:34.755
that if I saved saying, "Thank you,"
"I'm sorry," or "I love you,"

44:34.838 --> 44:35.923
I'd regret it later.

44:37.883 --> 44:38.717
Really?

44:40.386 --> 44:41.387
Thanks.

44:42.096 --> 44:45.557
Wow, Madam Park. You're quick to learn.

44:45.641 --> 44:47.976
I never save such expressions anyway.

44:50.646 --> 44:51.563
Oh, right.

44:52.147 --> 44:54.066
Where's the gift box you prepared?

44:54.650 --> 44:56.360
The meat? Why do you ask?

44:56.443 --> 44:58.153
I'll go give it to him.

44:59.154 --> 45:02.699
I came to think it wasn't his fault.

45:05.494 --> 45:07.246
Oh, goodness.

45:10.040 --> 45:12.835
You keep turning out better
the more I see you.

45:22.219 --> 45:24.096
Oh, welcome. Come have a seat.

45:26.515 --> 45:27.641
Welcome.

45:27.724 --> 45:29.184
Goodness. Have a seat here.

45:33.730 --> 45:36.024
My mother told me

45:36.942 --> 45:39.528
that you tried hard to help my father.

45:41.155 --> 45:44.491
I know it's late, but thank you so much.

45:44.575 --> 45:45.909
No, don't mention it.

45:46.743 --> 45:48.745
I'm the one who owes you
a belated apology.

45:49.246 --> 45:50.831
I heard when you applied for Taebaek,

45:50.914 --> 45:53.333
my employees were
very disrespectful to you.

45:54.543 --> 45:57.629
I'm all right. Please don't mind it.

46:00.382 --> 46:03.427
Why don't you join Taebaek
if it's not too late?

46:03.510 --> 46:04.928
This is an official offer.

46:05.512 --> 46:08.515
Thank you for your offer,
but I'm afraid I have to decline.

46:09.808 --> 46:12.769
I have clients to help.

46:12.853 --> 46:15.022
Oh, I see.

46:19.109 --> 46:20.235
How about this?

46:20.944 --> 46:23.697
If you ever face something
too difficult to handle alone,

46:23.780 --> 46:24.823
ask me for help anytime.

46:26.533 --> 46:29.495
Honestly, I'm doing this for your father.

46:30.746 --> 46:34.166
Gi-jung would've done the same
if it'd been the other way around.

46:35.501 --> 46:38.295
I understand. I'll do as you say.

46:41.173 --> 46:42.716
You grew up to be a fine young man.

46:45.886 --> 46:47.513
Gi-jung must be happy.

46:58.690 --> 47:01.818
Don't tell me
you're planning to join Taebaek.

47:03.237 --> 47:04.446
I mean,

47:04.988 --> 47:06.990
it's not necessary
for us to work together.

47:07.074 --> 47:08.742
Don't worry.

47:08.825 --> 47:10.661
I'm not joining Taebaek.

47:11.745 --> 47:13.121
Good thinking.

47:13.872 --> 47:16.625
My father has become soft with age,

47:17.626 --> 47:21.338
but an attorney like you
doesn't suit Taebaek at all.

47:31.890 --> 47:34.434
Was the pen safely delivered to you?

47:36.061 --> 47:36.979
Pen?

47:37.938 --> 47:42.234
<i>You follow me from behind</i>
<i>But I race forward</i>

47:46.280 --> 47:49.575
With all due respect,
stay out of my business.

47:50.534 --> 47:51.410
What?

48:11.513 --> 48:13.724
Attorney Han? What are you doing here?

48:16.810 --> 48:17.894
I waited for you.

48:19.187 --> 48:20.814
Me? Why?

48:22.399 --> 48:24.026
Do you have time on Saturday evening?

48:24.901 --> 48:26.320
It's my birthday.

48:27.029 --> 48:27.904
Care to be with me?

48:31.283 --> 48:34.036
You want to be with me
on the evening of your birthday?

48:35.162 --> 48:36.038
Yes.

48:36.705 --> 48:37.748
At my parents' house.

48:39.583 --> 48:40.959
At your parents'?

48:43.211 --> 48:45.505
I'm planning to make seaweed soup
for my mom.

48:46.131 --> 48:47.466
I used to do it before.

48:49.551 --> 48:51.261
That's a good idea.

48:52.054 --> 48:54.097
But why do you need me?

48:54.765 --> 48:55.766
Oh.

48:56.308 --> 48:59.436
My sister hasn't gotten
to have the kimchi stew yet.

49:00.145 --> 49:02.898
Oh, that pork kimchi stew?

49:03.398 --> 49:07.152
I'd appreciate your help
if you don't like kimchi stew.

49:09.696 --> 49:13.158
Well, all Koreans love kimchi stew.

49:14.451 --> 49:15.327
Sure.

49:17.996 --> 49:19.331
-This?
-Yes.

49:22.459 --> 49:23.669
-No, not that.
-No?

49:23.752 --> 49:25.837
Lettuce, perilla leaves…

49:25.921 --> 49:27.714
-Let's take a small pack.
-A small one?

49:29.257 --> 49:31.259
This? No?

49:40.852 --> 49:41.812
This is it.

49:45.607 --> 49:47.401
I used to feel so suffocated here,

49:48.110 --> 49:49.194
but I'm at ease now.

50:00.080 --> 50:01.039
Na-hyun.

50:02.666 --> 50:03.792
-Welcome.
-Hello.

50:03.875 --> 50:04.918
Hello.

50:06.002 --> 50:07.921
This is Attorney Shin I-rang.

50:08.004 --> 50:09.798
We're colleagues.
There's nothing between us.

50:10.465 --> 50:12.926
Oh, I see.

50:13.009 --> 50:14.302
We didn't say anything.

50:14.386 --> 50:15.846
Come on inside.

50:15.929 --> 50:17.764
-You bought so much.
-It's nothing.

50:24.104 --> 50:26.481
Na-hyun, don't make it too salty.

50:26.565 --> 50:27.941
No, it's fine.

50:28.024 --> 50:30.610
Just relax. You're a guest here.

50:31.570 --> 50:32.571
It's all right.

50:41.913 --> 50:43.790
ALLERGY MEDICINE

50:47.002 --> 50:49.963
Here comes Na-hyun's braised <i>galbi</i>.

50:50.046 --> 50:52.674
Wow. This is outstanding.

50:54.384 --> 50:55.343
Thank you for the meal.

50:55.427 --> 50:56.803
-Enjoy.
-Let's eat.

50:56.887 --> 50:58.597
I'll enjoy.

51:23.789 --> 51:25.040
This is so good.

51:25.749 --> 51:26.875
Is it?

51:42.933 --> 51:43.767
Do you like it?

51:45.310 --> 51:46.353
I love it.

51:48.605 --> 51:49.439
Here.

51:54.027 --> 51:55.320
It's really good.

51:56.363 --> 51:57.405
Help yourself.

52:19.761 --> 52:20.762
So-hyun.

52:21.304 --> 52:23.014
What is it, Na-hyun?

52:24.391 --> 52:25.725
Actually,

52:27.352 --> 52:29.437
I became an attorney because of you.

52:32.691 --> 52:35.068
I knew it, Han Na-hyun.

52:39.531 --> 52:41.825
Something has been on my mind lately,

52:43.910 --> 52:48.164
but what do you think
the best attorney is?

52:56.506 --> 52:57.924
That's my dream.

53:00.427 --> 53:01.428
You

53:03.013 --> 53:05.473
will be a good attorney for sure.

53:07.893 --> 53:09.019
I believe you will.

53:29.664 --> 53:31.082
You have a picture of me too?

53:49.434 --> 53:50.727
MONOPOLY

54:04.574 --> 54:06.076
MESSAGES
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

54:06.910 --> 54:08.036
<i>Na-hyun.</i>

54:08.620 --> 54:10.789
<i>Now is my time to use the golden key</i>

54:10.872 --> 54:12.040
<i>from the other day.</i>

54:13.166 --> 54:15.585
<i>I want to go to where I belong.</i>

54:27.222 --> 54:30.433
<i>I'm sending my farewell via text.</i>

54:32.018 --> 54:34.729
<i>The past few days with you</i>

54:34.813 --> 54:36.606
<i>felt like a picnic.</i>

54:36.690 --> 54:38.358
<i>I had such a blast.</i>

54:39.609 --> 54:42.404
<i>So, please don't be sad.</i>

54:45.031 --> 54:46.199
<i>I want you to remember</i>

54:47.200 --> 54:48.994
<i>that even if I pass on,</i>

54:49.536 --> 54:52.038
<i>I'll always be in your heart.</i>

54:53.373 --> 54:55.750
<i>Until the day we meet again,</i>

54:56.251 --> 54:57.419
<i>take care.</i>

54:59.045 --> 55:00.005
<i>Na-hyun,</i>

55:01.256 --> 55:02.257
<i>I love you.</i>

55:06.720 --> 55:09.222
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

55:20.150 --> 55:21.359
Thank you so much.

55:25.030 --> 55:26.448
Wherever I go,

55:27.323 --> 55:29.117
I won't forget about you.

55:29.951 --> 55:31.161
So-hyun.

55:31.244 --> 55:32.495
Mister,

55:33.705 --> 55:34.706
you certainly are

55:36.332 --> 55:37.834
the best attorney ever.

55:41.254 --> 55:43.131
I was truly happy

55:44.132 --> 55:45.258
to have an attorney…

55:47.886 --> 55:49.012
like you.

55:55.518 --> 55:56.519
Look.

55:58.938 --> 56:01.149
Is it right to pass on like this?

56:02.776 --> 56:04.360
I can't help but think

56:04.444 --> 56:07.447
that it's wrong to pass on
without letting your sister know.

56:07.530 --> 56:08.740
I don't want

56:09.657 --> 56:11.951
to break her heart anymore.

56:13.244 --> 56:16.081
I understand, but…

56:21.294 --> 56:22.754
You should know

56:23.755 --> 56:25.965
it's a true blessing
to be able to say your final goodbyes

56:27.258 --> 56:28.802
in person.

56:30.178 --> 56:32.180
It's actually not because of Na-hyun.

56:33.306 --> 56:34.307
It's just an excuse.

56:36.267 --> 56:38.645
I might not be able to hold back myself.

56:39.979 --> 56:41.064
I'm scared…

56:43.441 --> 56:44.984
I might beg to stay

56:46.402 --> 56:48.613
hanging on while in tears…

56:50.782 --> 56:52.450
and end up…

56:56.496 --> 56:57.705
breaking her heart.

57:03.044 --> 57:04.003
I see.

57:06.297 --> 57:08.299
It was thoughtless of me.

57:09.634 --> 57:10.885
Take good care

57:12.053 --> 57:13.054
of Na-hyun…

57:15.557 --> 57:16.850
for me,

57:19.727 --> 57:20.812
please.

57:45.920 --> 57:46.754
So-hyun.

57:47.755 --> 57:48.756
So-hyun.

57:50.758 --> 57:52.093
Where's So-hyun?

57:52.594 --> 57:54.095
She can't leave just yet.

57:55.221 --> 57:58.224
She's… still here.

58:02.979 --> 58:03.855
Na-hyun.

58:15.366 --> 58:16.534
So-hyun.

58:22.916 --> 58:25.168
Thank you for coming to me.

58:28.046 --> 58:29.547
For the past few days,

58:31.257 --> 58:33.009
I was unbelievably happy.

58:35.470 --> 58:37.013
With this memory,

58:38.681 --> 58:40.099
I'll live

58:41.267 --> 58:42.894
a happy life.

58:44.812 --> 58:45.772
I was…

58:50.568 --> 58:51.903
happy too,

58:53.530 --> 58:54.614
Na-hyun.

58:59.494 --> 59:00.703
I'll go now.

59:17.595 --> 59:18.721
Na-hyun.

59:49.002 --> 59:51.296
You be happy too, So-hyun.

59:57.343 --> 59:58.469
And please…

01:00:01.139 --> 01:00:03.141
be my younger sister in our next lives.

01:00:05.184 --> 01:00:06.894
I'll protect you then.

01:00:09.314 --> 01:00:10.523
You little brat.

01:00:12.400 --> 01:00:14.277
Na-hyun, you will

01:00:15.236 --> 01:00:16.321
be my younger sister again…

01:00:19.866 --> 01:00:21.326
in our next lives.

01:00:28.875 --> 01:00:30.668
Don't worry about me,

01:00:33.546 --> 01:00:35.465
and live happily…

01:00:42.513 --> 01:00:43.598
until…

01:00:47.226 --> 01:00:48.353
the day…

01:00:48.436 --> 01:00:49.354
The day

01:00:50.396 --> 01:00:51.773
-we meet again.
-…we meet again.

01:01:43.991 --> 01:01:45.785
Are you feeling better?

01:01:47.787 --> 01:01:48.705
Yes.

01:01:49.789 --> 01:01:52.417
I think I can let her go now.

01:01:53.668 --> 01:01:54.794
Thank you.

01:02:08.891 --> 01:02:10.810
So-hyun said you'd need this.

01:02:11.519 --> 01:02:12.729
She picked it herself.

01:02:18.776 --> 01:02:19.861
Thanks.

01:02:23.656 --> 01:02:26.409
I won't forget how grateful I am.

01:02:26.492 --> 01:02:28.202
Stop it now.

01:02:28.286 --> 01:02:30.413
You might end up spoiling me.

01:02:32.707 --> 01:02:35.168
Oh, I didn't show you this picture, did I?

01:02:35.251 --> 01:02:36.294
What picture?

01:02:41.632 --> 01:02:43.176
This wasn't So-hyun.

01:02:43.259 --> 01:02:45.052
She'd never get scared like this.

01:02:46.262 --> 01:02:48.973
You put up with it for me, didn't you?

01:02:50.308 --> 01:02:51.517
No, I didn't.

01:02:52.143 --> 01:02:55.563
I… love roller coaster rides.

01:02:56.981 --> 01:02:58.941
What do you say
to another ride tomorrow, then?

01:02:59.025 --> 01:02:59.984
W-What?

01:03:05.490 --> 01:03:06.449
Well,

01:03:07.575 --> 01:03:10.119
I have something to ask you.

01:03:11.329 --> 01:03:12.330
What is it?

01:03:15.416 --> 01:03:16.417
It's…

01:03:19.837 --> 01:03:21.130
Tell me.

01:03:21.214 --> 01:03:23.216
Given my mood,
I'm willing to do anything you ask.

01:03:29.847 --> 01:03:30.890
Will you…

01:03:35.102 --> 01:03:36.771
stay with me?

01:03:38.439 --> 01:03:39.398
What?

01:03:45.822 --> 01:03:46.989
I mean,

01:03:47.073 --> 01:03:49.408
you don't have an office.

01:03:49.492 --> 01:03:52.119
We can share an office until you get one.

01:03:53.204 --> 01:03:55.581
And help each other when we're busy?

01:03:56.457 --> 01:03:58.042
That's not bad.

01:04:03.047 --> 01:04:03.881
Sure.

01:04:19.230 --> 01:04:22.316
Is there anything I need to know
before working with you,

01:04:22.400 --> 01:04:23.776
Mr. Ghost-seeing Attorney?

01:04:26.279 --> 01:04:27.363
I'm not sure.

01:04:28.155 --> 01:04:29.282
What could there be?

01:04:29.866 --> 01:04:33.369
You don't seem to remember a thing
once you're possessed.

01:04:34.120 --> 01:04:35.162
That's true.

01:04:35.246 --> 01:04:37.707
I can't remember anything
that happens while I'm possessed.

01:04:37.790 --> 01:04:39.000
Can I cuss you out?

01:04:39.083 --> 01:04:40.001
Excuse me?

01:05:46.317 --> 01:05:48.319
SHIN I-RANG, HAN NA-HYUN
LAW OFFICE

01:06:19.392 --> 01:06:20.476
<i>What brings you here?</i>

01:06:20.559 --> 01:06:22.561
<i>Because of my late husband.</i>

01:06:22.645 --> 01:06:25.314
I'm Kang Dong-sik, the shoemaker.

01:06:25.398 --> 01:06:26.440
He had Alzheimer's.

01:06:26.524 --> 01:06:27.358
Oh, my head!

01:06:27.441 --> 01:06:28.693
What was this again?

01:06:28.776 --> 01:06:31.737
My mother thinks it's only right
to do as my father's will says.

01:06:31.821 --> 01:06:33.489
Who could it be that wrote the will?

01:06:33.572 --> 01:06:35.366
<i>I can't remember.</i>

01:06:35.449 --> 01:06:38.661
<i>Ms. Chae Jeong-hui has proved it</i>
<i>to be her husband's handwriting.</i>

01:06:38.744 --> 01:06:40.121
She has no reason to fabricate the will.

01:06:40.204 --> 01:06:41.831
<i>If the chairman's will is genuine.</i>

01:06:41.914 --> 01:06:43.207
Say what must be said!

01:06:43.290 --> 01:06:44.583
Not now, please.

01:06:44.667 --> 01:06:49.672
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
